Case #1 in B.C.[British Columbia: born Pakistan 18 Dec 1996; arrived
Canada August 1998; case reported on 4 Sep 1998.
Case #2 in Ontario: 78 year old female, traveled to Equatorial Guinea from
14 Aug to
4 Sep 1998. Hospitalized on return, diganosis confirmed on 9 Sep 1998.
Both were _V. cholerae_ O1 Ogawa.
Delay in reporting to WHO due to obtaining all data from provinces.
